#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:27
msgid "Convenient syntax for JavaScript library functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:29
msgid ""
"This allows you to declare JavaScript in your C code as a function, which "
"can be called like a normal C function. For example, the following C program "
"would display two alerts if it was compiled with Emscripten and run in the "
"browser:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:45
msgid ""
"Arguments can be passed as normal C arguments, and have the same name in the "
"JavaScript code. These arguments can either be of type ``int32_t`` or "
"``double``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:60
msgid ""
"Null-terminated C strings can also be passed into ``EM_JS`` functions, but "
"to operate on them, they need to be copied out from the heap to convert to "
"high-level JavaScript strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:70
msgid ""
"In the same manner, pointers to any type (including ``void *``) can be "
"passed inside ``EM_JS`` code, where they appear as integers like ``char *`` "
"pointers above did. Accessing the data can be managed by reading the heap "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:86
msgid ""
"In addition, EM_JS functions can return a value back to C code. The output "
"value is passed back with a ``return`` statement:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:105
#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:184
msgid ""
"Strings can be returned back to C from JavaScript, but one needs to be "
"careful about memory management."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:127
msgid "Convenient syntax for inline assembly/JavaScript."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:129
msgid ""
"This allows you to declare JavaScript in your C code \"inline\", which is "
"then executed when your compiled code is run in the browser. For example, "
"the following C code would display two alerts if it was compiled with "
"Emscripten and run in the browser:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:135
msgid ""
"Arguments can be passed inside the JavaScript code block, where they arrive "
"as variables ``$0``, ``$1`` etc. These arguments can either be of type "
"``int32_t`` or ``double``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:143
msgid "Note the ``{`` and ``}``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:145
msgid ""
"Null-terminated C strings can also be passed into ``EM_ASM`` blocks, but to "
"operate on them, they need to be copied out from the heap to convert to high-"
"level JavaScript strings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:151
msgid ""
"In the same manner, pointers to any type (including ``void *``) can be "
"passed inside ``EM_ASM`` code, where they appear as integers like ``char *`` "
"pointers above did. Accessing the data can be managed by reading the heap "
"directly."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:161
msgid ""
"As of Emscripten ``1.30.4``, the contents of ``EM_ASM`` code blocks appear "
"inside the normal JS file, and as result, Closure compiler and other "
"JavaScript minifiers will be able to operate on them. You may need to use "
"safety quotes in some places (``a['b']`` instead of ``a.b``) to avoid "
"minification from occurring."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:162
msgid ""
"The C preprocessor does not have an understanding of JavaScript tokens, and "
"as a result, if the ``code`` block contains a comma character ``,``, it may "
"be necessary to wrap the code block inside parentheses. For example, code "
"``EM_ASM(return [1,2,3].length);`` will not compile, but ``EM_ASM((return "
"[1,2,3].length));`` does."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:166
msgid ""
"This macro, as well as :c:macro:`EM_ASM_DOUBLE` and :c:macro:`EM_ASM_PTR`, "
"behave like :c:macro:`EM_ASM`, but in addition they also return a value back "
"to C code. The output value is passed back with a ``return`` statement:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:180
msgid ""
"Similar to :c:macro:`EM_ASM_INT` but for a pointer-sized return values. When "
"building with ``-sMEMORY64`` this results in i64 return value, otherwise it "
"results in an i32 return value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:201
msgid "Similar to :c:macro:`EM_ASM_INT` but for a ``double`` return value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:205
msgid ""
"This behaves like :c:macro:`EM_ASM`, but does the call on the main thread. "
"This is useful in a pthreads build, when you want to interact with the DOM "
"from a pthread; this basically proxies the call for you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:209
msgid ""
"This call is proxied in a synchronous way to the main thread, that is, "
"execution will resume after the main thread has finished running the JS. "
"Synchronous proxying also makes it possible to return a value, see the next "
"two variants."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:216
msgid "Similar to :c:macro:`MAIN_THREAD_EM_ASM` but returns an ``int`` value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:220
msgid ""
"Similar to :c:macro:`MAIN_THREAD_EM_ASM` but returns a ``double`` value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:224
msgid "Similar to :c:macro:`MAIN_THREAD_EM_ASM` but returns a pointer value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/emscripten.h.rst:228
msgid ""
"Similar to :c:macro:`MAIN_THREAD_EM_ASM` but is proxied in an "
"**asynchronous** way, that is, the main thread will receive a request to run "
"the code, and will run it when it can; the worker will not wait for that. "
"(Note that if this is called on the main thread, then there is nothing to "
"proxy, and the JS is executed immediately and synchronously.)"
msgstr ""

